<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,476,501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[381,429,477,501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">type</typeStatus>
specimen was collected in bush. The new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Macquart)" authorityName="Macquart" baseAuthorityName="Macquart" baseAuthorityYear="1842" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis box="[1313,1436,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">A. pusillus</emphasis>
(Macquart)
</taxonomicName>
distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[442,540,511,536]" name="Pakistan" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[551,609,511,536]" name="India" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">India</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[664,734,511,536]" name="Nepal" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, but may be separated from the latter by the size of the cercus and shape of the surstylus. In 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Macquart" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[484,602,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusillus">
<emphasis box="[484,602,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">A. pusillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the cercus is distinctly longer than the epandrium, and the surstylus is not bifurcated (
<bibRefCitation author="Yang, D. &amp; Zhang, L. &amp; Wang, M. &amp; Zhu, Y." box="[279,466,584,608]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="111 - 291" refId="ref25610" refString="Yang, D., Zhang, L., Wang, M. &amp; Zhu, Y. (2011) Fauna Sinica Insecta Uol. 53. Diptera Dolichopodidae. Science Press, Beijing, pp. 111 - 291." type="book chapter" year="2011">
Yang 
<emphasis box="[345,393,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 66).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
